---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="NeuroGym Review 2026: Is John Assaraf's Brain Training Worth It?"
  description="Honest NeuroGym review 2026. We tested John Assaraf's brain training programs. Full breakdown of pros, cons, pricing, and results."
  schema="review"
>
  <article class="py-16 bg-[#0D0D1A]">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="mb-10">
        <span class="text-xs font-bold text-[#7C3AED] bg-[#7C3AED]/10 px-3 py-1 rounded-full uppercase tracking-wider">In-Depth Review</span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mt-4 mb-4 leading-tight">
          NeuroGym Review 2026: Can John Assaraf's Brain Training Actually Rewire Your Mind?
        </h1>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-6 text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">
          <span>Updated: April 2026</span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span>12 min read</span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span class="text-yellow-400">★★★★★ 4.6/5</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          NeuroGym — founded by neuroscience entrepreneur John Assaraf — claims to use the latest brain science to help you overcome mental blocks, build winning habits, and achieve your biggest goals. After testing it thoroughly, here's our complete, honest verdict.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Quick Verdict Box -->
      <div class="bg-[#1A1A2E] border-l-4 border-[#D4AF37] rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Quick Verdict</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-green-400 font-bold mb-3">✅ Pros</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li>• Genuinely science-backed methodology</li>
              <li>• John Assaraf's credibility and expertise</li>
              <li>• Detailed neuroscience explanations</li>
              <li>• Strong community and coaching support</li>
              <li>• Focused specifically on overcoming mental blocks</li>
              <li>• Multiple program formats (audio, video, live)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-red-400 font-bold mb-3">❌ Cons</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li>• Premium pricing can be steep</li>
              <li>• First payout after 6-month delay (affiliates)</li>
              <li>• Less variety than platforms like Mindvalley</li>
              <li>• Requires consistent daily commitment</li>
              <li>• Limited free trial content</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-gray-700 flex items-center justify-between">
          <div>
            <div class="text-[#D4AF37] text-3xl font-bold">4.6 / 5</div>
            <div class="text-yellow-400 text-xl">★★★★★</div>
          </div>
          <a href="[NEUROGYM_AFFILIATE_LINK]" class="bg-gradient-to-r from-[#D4AF37] to-[#7C3AED] text-white font-bold py-3 px-8 rounded-xl hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity">
            Visit NeuroGym →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Main Review Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">What Is NeuroGym?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          NeuroGym is a personal development company founded by John Assaraf, a neuroscience-minded entrepreneur best known for his appearance in the documentary "The Secret" and his bestselling books including "Having It All" and "The Answer."
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          What sets NeuroGym apart from generic personal development programs is its explicit focus on the neuroscience of behavior change. The programs are built around a concept Assaraf calls "Innercise" — mental exercises designed to specifically target and retrain the neural patterns that keep you stuck.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          The flagship product is the <strong class="text-white">NeuroGym Inner Circle</strong> — a subscription-based membership that gives you access to Assaraf's core programs, monthly live coaching calls, and a private community of like-minded individuals committed to growth.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">The Science Behind NeuroGym</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The foundation of NeuroGym's approach is neuroplasticity — the brain's proven ability to rewire itself through repeated thought patterns and behaviors. Modern neuroscience has confirmed that we can physically change our brain's structure and function through deliberate mental practice.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          NeuroGym programs focus on:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 mb-6 ml-6">
          <li><strong class="text-[#D4AF37]">Identifying limiting beliefs</strong> — Surface and neutralize the subconscious programming holding you back</li>
          <li><strong class="text-[#D4AF37]">Pattern interrupts</strong> — Break old neural loops that trigger self-sabotaging behaviors</li>
          <li><strong class="text-[#D4AF37]">Emotional regulation</strong> — Build the emotional intelligence to stay focused under pressure</li>
          <li><strong class="text-[#D4AF37]">Visualization and mental rehearsal</strong> — A technique used by elite athletes and performers to program success</li>
          <li><strong class="text-[#D4AF37]">Daily "Innercise" practices</strong> — Short, targeted brain exercises that compound over time</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Key Programs Offered</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8 not-prose">
          {[
            { name: "Winning the Game of Money", desc: "NeuroGym's most popular program. Uses brain training techniques specifically targeting money mindset and financial success.", price: "$97–$497" },
            { name: "Winning the Game of Fear", desc: "Overcome the fears and anxieties that keep you playing small. Combines exposure therapy principles with neuroscience.", price: "$97–$297" },
            { name: "Winning the Game of Weight Loss", desc: "A neurologically-based approach to healthy habits and sustainable body transformation.", price: "$97–$297" },
            { name: "Inner Circle Membership", desc: "Monthly membership with access to all programs, live coaching, and community support.", price: "$97/month" },
          ].map(prog => (
            <div class="bg-[#1A1A2E] rounded-xl p-6 border border-gray-700">
              <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-lg mb-2">{prog.name}</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-3">{prog.desc}</p>
              <span class="text-[#D4AF37] font-semibold text-sm">{prog.price}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Who Is NeuroGym Best For?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          NeuroGym is particularly well-suited for people who:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6 ml-6">
          <li>✅ Have tried other programs but keep "self-sabotaging"</li>
          <li>✅ Want a more scientific, evidence-based approach to personal development</li>
          <li>✅ Struggle with money mindset, fear, or deeply ingrained limiting beliefs</li>
          <li>✅ Are willing to commit to daily mental practice (even just 10-15 minutes)</li>
          <li>✅ Appreciate community support alongside self-directed learning</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          It's less suited to people looking for broad skills training (like Mindvalley) or those who want quick, surface-level motivational content. NeuroGym digs deep into the why behind your behaviors — which takes some patience and commitment.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Real Results: What Members Report</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Member testimonials consistently report several categories of change after completing NeuroGym programs:
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 mb-8 not-prose">
          {[
            { quote: "I'd tried everything — therapy, books, other courses. NeuroGym was the first program that actually helped me understand why I kept sabotaging my income. Within 90 days, I'd broken through a 3-year income ceiling.", name: "Marcus T.", role: "Entrepreneur" },
            { quote: "The daily Innercise practices felt awkward at first, but after about 2-3 weeks I genuinely noticed my thoughts had shifted. I was calmer, more focused, and stopped procrastinating on the things that mattered most.", name: "Sarah L.", role: "Marketing Director" },
          ].map(t => (
            <div class="bg-[#1A1A2E] rounded-xl p-6 border-l-4 border-[#D4AF37]">
              <p class="text-gray-300 italic mb-4">"{t.quote}"</p>
              <div>
                <p class="text-white font-bold">{t.name}</p>
                <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">{t.role}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Pricing Overview</h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8 not-prose">
          <table class="w-full text-left bg-[#1A1A2E] rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
            <thead class="bg-[#D4AF37]/20">
              <tr>
                <th class="px-6 py-4 text-white font-bold">Program</th>
                <th class="px-6 py-4 text-white font-bold">Price</th>
                <th class="px-6 py-4 text-white font-bold">Best For</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {[
                { prog: "Individual Programs", price: "$97–$497", best: "Targeting a specific area" },
                { prog: "Inner Circle Monthly", price: "$97/month", best: "Ongoing coaching + community" },
                { prog: "Inner Circle Annual", price: "$797/year", best: "Best value for committed learners" },
              ].map((row, i) => (
                <tr class={i % 2 === 0 ? "bg-[#1A1A2E]" : "bg-[#0D0D1A]"}>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-300">{row.prog}</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 text-[#D4AF37] font-semibold">{row.price}</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-400">{row.best}</td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Final Verdict</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          NeuroGym is one of the most genuinely science-backed personal development programs available. If you're serious about understanding the neuroscience of behavior change — and willing to put in the daily mental work — it delivers real results that more surface-level programs simply can't match.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          It's not the cheapest option, and it requires genuine commitment. But for people who have tried other programs without lasting results, NeuroGym's brain-first approach is often the missing piece.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Final CTA -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-[#D4AF37]/20 to-[#7C3AED]/20 rounded-2xl p-10 text-center border border-[#D4AF37]/30 mt-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Ready to Train Your Brain for Success?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 mb-8 text-lg">Join thousands of people who have used NeuroGym to break through their mental limits.</p>
        <a href="[NEUROGYM_AFFILIATE_LINK]" class="inline-block bg-gradient-to-r from-[#D4AF37] to-[#7C3AED] text-white font-bold py-4 px-12 rounded-xl text-lg hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity">
          Start With NeuroGym →
        </a>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-4">*Affiliate link — we may earn a commission at no cost to you</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
